-- Cameroon’s Average Cocoa Exports Dropped 0.7% in Week
-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 2012-03-13T09:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/cameroon-s-average-cocoa-exports-dropped-0-7-in-week-table-.html
The average price for cocoa exports
from  Cameroon ,  Africa ’s fourth-biggest producer of the main
chocolate ingredient, fell by 0.7 percent 1,072  CFA francs  a
kilogram (2.2 pounds) in the week to March 12.  The West African country has exported 149,792 metric tons
of the crop since the season started in August, according to a
mobile-phone text message from the Cocoa and Coffee Board today.
The following is a table of free-on-board export rates at the
port of Douala in CFA francs per kilogram.  
